---
export const prerender = true;
import BlogLayout from '../../layouts/BlogLayout.astro';
import '../../styles/global.css';
---

<BlogLayout
  title="Scrabble Words With Double B — CABBAGE, SCRIBBLE, BOBBIN & More"
  description="Best double-B words for Scrabble. CABBAGE (14pts), SCRIBBLE (14pts), BOBBIN (12pts). BB pattern strategy for solid mid-game plays. Free word finder."
  keywords="scrabble double b words, cabbage scrabble, scribble scrabble, bobbin scrabble, bb words scrabble, double b strategy, double letter words"
>
  <script type="application/ld+json" set:html={JSON.stringify({
    "@context": "https://schema.org", "@type": "Article",
    "headline": "Scrabble Words With Double B — CABBAGE, SCRIBBLE, BOBBIN & More",
    "description": "Best double-B Scrabble words. BB pattern strategy for solid mid-game plays.",
    "datePublished": "2026-06-30",
    "author": { "@type": "Organization", "name": "ScrabbleWordsFinder.com", "url": "https://www.scrabblewordsfinder.com" },
    "publisher": { "@type": "Organization", "name": "ScrabbleWordsFinder.com" },
    "mainEntityOfPage": { "@type": "WebPage", "@id": "https://www.scrabblewordsfinder.com/blog/scrabble-words-with-double-b" }
  })} />
  <script type="application/ld+json" set:html={JSON.stringify({
    "@context": "https://schema.org", "@type": "FAQPage",
    "mainEntity": [
      { "@type": "Question", "name": "What are the best double-B words?", "acceptedAnswer": { "@type": "Answer", "text": "CABBAGE (14pts, 7 letters bingo), SCRIBBLE (14pts, 8 letters), and BOBBIN (12pts). B=3pts each gives BB pairs 6 base points." } },
      { "@type": "Question", "name": "How many B tiles are in Scrabble?", "acceptedAnswer": { "@type": "Answer", "text": "2 B tiles (3pts each). Drawing both is uncommon but gives exclusive BB word access worth 6 points from the pair." } },
      { "@type": "Question", "name": "What short BB words work?", "acceptedAnswer": { "@type": "Answer", "text": "ABB (7pts), EBB (7pts), ABBOT (9pts). RABBIT (10pts) and GIBBET (11pts) offer mid-length options." } }
    ]
  })} />

  <div class="max-w-3xl mx-auto px-4 py-12">
    <article class="prose prose-invert prose-gray max-w-none">
      <nav class="text-sm text-gray-400 mb-6 not-prose flex items-center gap-1">
        <a href="/blog/" class="hover:text-blue-400 transition-colors">← Blog</a><span class="mx-1">›</span><span class="text-gray-300">Word Lists</span>
      </nav>
      <h1 class="text-3xl font-bold text-white mb-4">Scrabble Words With Double B — CABBAGE, SCRIBBLE, BOBBIN & More</h1>
      <div class="not-prose mb-8 flex items-center gap-3 text-sm text-gray-400">
        <time datetime="2026-06-30">June 30, 2026</time><span class="w-1 h-1 rounded-full bg-gray-600"></span><span>4 min read</span><span class="w-1 h-1 rounded-full bg-gray-600"></span>
        <a href="/" class="inline-flex items-center gap-1 text-blue-400 hover:underline"><span aria-hidden="true">🔤</span> Word Finder</a>
      </div>
      <p class="text-lg leading-relaxed text-gray-300 mb-8">Two B tiles in the bag, each worth 3 points — drawing both gives you 6 points from BB alone. Double-B words are often everyday vocabulary, making them easy to spot on your rack.</p>

      <div class="not-prose my-6 p-4 rounded-xl border border-amber-500/30 bg-amber-950/10">
        <div class="flex flex-wrap items-center justify-center gap-6 text-center">
          <div><p class="text-xl font-bold text-amber-400">14 pts</p><p class="text-xs text-gray-400">CABBAGE</p></div>
          <div><p class="text-xl font-bold text-amber-400">14 pts</p><p class="text-xs text-gray-400">SCRIBBLE</p></div>
          <div><p class="text-xl font-bold text-amber-400">12 pts</p><p class="text-xs text-gray-400">BOBBIN</p></div>
          <div><p class="text-xl font-bold text-amber-400">2</p><p class="text-xs text-gray-400">B tiles in bag</p></div>
        </div>
      </div>

      <h2 class="text-xl font-light text-blue-400 mt-10 mb-4 border-l-4 border-blue-400 pl-4">Top Double-B Words</h2>

      <div class="not-prose my-8 p-6 rounded-2xl border-2 border-amber-500/50 bg-gradient-to-r from-amber-950/30 to-yellow-950/20 relative overflow-hidden">
        <div class="absolute top-3 right-4 text-xs font-bold uppercase tracking-widest text-amber-500/70">👑 Top BB Words</div>
        <p class="text-2xl font-black text-white tracking-wider mb-2">CABBAGE — 14 Points</p>
        <p class="text-sm text-amber-300 font-semibold mb-3">C=3, A=1, B=3, B=3, A=1, G=2, E=1 · 7 letters · Bingo eligible</p>
        <p class="text-sm text-gray-300 leading-relaxed">C=3 plus BB=6 plus G=2 gives CABBAGE strong base scoring. With bingo bonus it delivers 64 total points.</p>
      </div>

      <div class="not-prose my-6 grid grid-cols-1 sm:grid-cols-2 gap-4">
        <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-amber-500/30 bg-amber-950/10"><p class="text-amber-400 font-semibold text-sm mb-1">✍️ SCRIBBLE</p><p class="text-xs text-gray-400">14 pts · 8 letters · C=3 + BB · Bingo</p></div>
        <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-amber-500/30 bg-amber-950/10"><p class="text-amber-400 font-semibold text-sm mb-1">🧵 BOBBIN</p><p class="text-xs text-gray-400">12 pts · 6 letters · B+O+BB+I+N</p></div>
        <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-amber-500/30 bg-amber-950/10"><p class="text-amber-400 font-semibold text-sm mb-1">🐰 RABBIT</p><p class="text-xs text-gray-400">10 pts · 6 letters · BB mid-word</p></div>
        <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-amber-500/30 bg-amber-950/10"><p class="text-amber-400 font-semibold text-sm mb-1">🫧 BUBBLE</p><p class="text-xs text-gray-400">12 pts · 6 letters · Needs blank for 3rd B</p></div>
      </div>

      <h2 class="text-xl font-light text-blue-400 mt-10 mb-4 border-l-4 border-blue-400 pl-4">BB Pattern Strategy</h2>

      <div class="not-prose my-6 grid grid-cols-1 gap-4">
        <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-purple-500/30 bg-purple-950/20 hover:border-purple-400 transition-colors"><p class="text-sm text-gray-300"><span class="text-purple-400 font-semibold">-ABBLE and -IBBLE endings:</span> SCRABBLE, DRIBBLE, SCRIBBLE, BABBLE — familiar endings that create 7-8 letter bingo words.</p></div>
        <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-purple-500/30 bg-purple-950/20 hover:border-purple-400 transition-colors"><p class="text-sm text-gray-300"><span class="text-purple-400 font-semibold">EBB as a hook:</span> EBB (7pts) extends to EBBED, EBBING. Simple to play early and extend later for additional scoring.</p></div>
        <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-purple-500/30 bg-purple-950/20 hover:border-purple-400 transition-colors"><p class="text-sm text-gray-300"><span class="text-purple-400 font-semibold">BB + C/G combo:</span> CABBAGE (C+BB+G), COBBLER (C+BB), GOBBLER (G+BB) — pair BB with medium-value consonants for 12+ points.</p></div>
      </div>

      <div class="not-prose my-6 flex flex-wrap items-center justify-center gap-3">
        <span class="inline-flex items-center gap-1.5 px-3 py-1.5 rounded-lg bg-gray-800 border border-gray-700 text-sm"><span class="text-white font-bold">GIBBET</span><span class="text-blue-400 text-xs">11pts</span></span>
        <span class="inline-flex items-center gap-1.5 px-3 py-1.5 rounded-lg bg-gray-800 border border-gray-700 text-sm"><span class="text-white font-bold">COBBLER</span><span class="text-blue-400 text-xs">13pts</span></span>
        <span class="inline-flex items-center gap-1.5 px-3 py-1.5 rounded-lg bg-gray-800 border border-gray-700 text-sm"><span class="text-white font-bold">DRIBBLE</span><span class="text-blue-400 text-xs">12pts</span></span>
        <span class="inline-flex items-center gap-1.5 px-3 py-1.5 rounded-lg bg-gray-800 border border-gray-700 text-sm"><span class="text-white font-bold">HOBBIT</span><span class="text-blue-400 text-xs">13pts</span></span>
      </div>

      <div class="not-prose my-6 p-5 rounded-xl border border-blue-500/30 bg-blue-950/20">
        <p class="text-sm font-semibold text-blue-400 uppercase tracking-wider mb-2">💡 Familiarity Advantage</p>
        <p class="text-base text-gray-200">BB words are often <span class="text-white font-medium">everyday vocabulary</span> — RABBIT, CABBAGE, BUBBLE, HOBBY. You don't need obscure word knowledge to play them.</p>
      </div>

      <aside class="border-t border-gray-800 mt-12 pt-8 not-prose">
        <h3 class="text-sm font-semibold text-gray-400 uppercase tracking-wider mb-4">Related Articles</h3>
        <div class="grid gap-3">
          <a href="/blog/scrabble-words-with-double-t/" class="flex items-center gap-3 p-3 rounded-lg border border-gray-800 hover:border-blue-700 hover:bg-blue-900/10 transition-all group"><span class="text-blue-500 group-hover:translate-x-0.5 transition-transform">→</span><span class="text-sm text-gray-300 group-hover:text-blue-400 transition-colors">Scrabble Words With Double T</span></a>
          <a href="/blog/best-words-with-double-letters/" class="flex items-center gap-3 p-3 rounded-lg border border-gray-800 hover:border-blue-700 hover:bg-blue-900/10 transition-all group"><span class="text-blue-500 group-hover:translate-x-0.5 transition-transform">→</span><span class="text-sm text-gray-300 group-hover:text-blue-400 transition-colors">Best Words With Double Letters</span></a>
        </div>
      </aside>

      <div class="not-prose mt-10 p-5 bg-gradient-to-r from-blue-900/20 to-cyan-900/20 border border-blue-800 rounded-xl shadow-sm">
        <div class="flex items-center justify-between gap-4 flex-wrap">
          <p class="text-sm text-blue-300 font-medium">🔤 Find double-B words from your tiles — free Scrabble solver, no sign-up</p>
          <a href="/" class="inline-flex items-center gap-2 px-4 py-2 rounded-lg bg-blue-600 hover:bg-blue-700 text-white text-sm font-semibold transition-colors shadow-sm">Open Word Finder →</a>
        </div>
      </div>
      <div class="not-prose mt-8 text-center"><a href="/blog/" class="text-sm text-gray-400 hover:text-blue-400 transition-colors">← Back to all articles</a></div>
    </article>
  </div>
</BlogLayout>
